<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Additional Information</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"> “The hand that writes for opioids is also the hand that writes for a bowel regimen”</span></span></span></span></span>
<ul style="list-style-type:circle">
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Senna </span></span></b><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">BID<b> + PEG </b>daily (up to TID)</span></span></span></span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">If severe constipation already developed, do above plus try <b>methylnaltrexone</b> </span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"> CF pts (at risk for distal intestinal obstructive syndrome or DIOS)</span></span></span></span></span>
<ul style="list-style-type:circle">
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Not treated as true obstruction but rather like constipation</span></span></span></span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">PEG (QID) or just order “golytely” prep as if for colonoscopy preparation</span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
